(y_n, y_n /(1 − γ )^{1/n})
y_n
\theta
 \Pr\left(y_n<\theta<\frac{y_n}{(1-\gamma)^{1/n}}\right) = \gamma. 
 \Pr\left(\theta<\frac{y_n}{(1-\gamma)^{1/n}}\right)=\Pr\left( \theta(1-\gamma)^{1/n} < y_n\right) = 1-\Pr\left( y_n < \theta(1-\gamma)^{1/n} \right). 
n
\theta(1-\gamma)^{1/n}
c
 \Pr(y_n < c) = \Pr(\text{All $n$ observations}<c) = \Big( \Pr(\text{A single observation}<c) \Big)^n = \left( \frac c\theta \right)^n. 
